"{\"uid\": \"thesouthafrican.com-sport-paris-olympics-2024-luxolo-adams-vows-legal-action-against-asa-after-paris-olympics-2024-exclusion-latest\", \"text\": \"Copyright Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd. All Rights Reserved.  thesouthafrican.com is a division of Blue Sky Publications Ltd. Reproduction without permission prohibited  Home\\u00bbSport\\u00bbParis Olympics 2024\\u00bbLuxolo Adams vows legal action against ASA after Paris Olympics 2024 exclusion  Sprinter Luxolo Adams has vowed legal action against ASA after he was cut from the South African Paris Olympics 2024 squad.  SprinterLuxolo Adamshas vowed legal action againstAthletics South Africa (ASA)after he was cut from the South AfricanParis Olympics 2024squad.  Adams, 27, was one of two casualties afterWayde van Niekerksensationally optedoutof the 400m to focus on the 200m event instead, as reported byThe South African website.  Fellow sprinterSinesipho Dambile, 22, also missed out on selection.  That decision meant there was no place for Adams in theTeam SAsquad - even though he has run a faster qualifying time in the half-lap event than Van Niekerk.  \\\"This decision has been incredibly disheartening, especially considering the journey I have undertaken and the mental and physical challenges I have faced,\\\" Adams said in astatement.  \\\"This decision came just three weeks before the Olympic Games and was communicated to me through an informal and distressing method, showing a lack of respect, professionalism, consistency, and lack of consideration for my mental health.  \\\"I am currently seeking urgent legal intervention to prevent ASA from removing me from the team which I qualified for,\\\" he said, \\\"and for them to be transparent and consistent\\u00a0in their processes and selection criteria.\\\"  ASA are able to selectthreeathletes to compete in the 200m event - provided they have obtained the qualifying mark.  Shaun MaswanganyiandBenjamin Richardsonare the other two athletes who will join Van Niekerk in attempting to bring home a medal in the event.  Truth be told, none of the trio stand any chance of doing so.  Van Niekerk's career best over the 200m distance is 19.84 which he set back in 2017, while Adams's personal best is 19.82 set in 2022.  Richardson's best 200m time is 19.99, the same as Maswanganyi.  No fewer than 17 different athletes have run under 20-seconds this year alone - and seven of them have posted sub-19.90 times.  Jamaica'sUsain Boltholds the 200m world record of 19.19 which he set in Berlin in 2009.  The Paris Olympics 2024 will start on27 July.  The heats of the men's 200m will take place on 5 August with the final scheduled for 8 August.  WIN R2 000: Take The South African's SASSA Survey  The South African is hiring! Freelance writing positions available  Follow The South African on Facebook for the latest local and international news  Follow The South African's WhatsApp channel for the latest sport, lifestyle and local news  Follow The South African on X for the latest, breaking news  A brand new shopping mall is coming to Pretoria East, bringing major retailers and new convenience to the area.  Orlando Pirates are reportedly set to welcome a new staff member in former Stellenbosch FC Head of Recruitment Brendon Fourie.  Masindi Nemtajela was stretched off during Orlando Pirates' 6-0 win over TS Galaxy on Sunday afternoon in Mbombela.  IT support is not just technical, it is personal.  Liema Pantsi's victory was clouded as fans of the 'Big Brother Mzansi' show expressed that Smash Afrika was unprofessional towards her.  A dominant weekend for the SA teams in the URC has made a big impact on the latest log standings as the playoffs edge closer.    TheSouthAfrican.com is all about South Africa and the stories that affect South Africans, wherever they are in the world.  We are independent.No agenda.No bias.  Our offices are for administrative purposes only, no visitors will be accepted without an appointment.  South Africa- Blue Sk